Vladimir Putin is coming under renewed pressure after Wagner Group forces were decimated in a key battlefield in the Ukraine war after being starved of ammunition. The group's owner Yevgeny Prigozhin, a close confidant of Russia's President, said forces in Bakhmut, Donetsk Oblast were killed on Tuesday due to "ammunition hunger". A picture of dozens of Wagner Group members killed has also emerged online. Tensions between Russia's military and Wagner surged on Tuesday after Prigozhin accused Moscow of starving his men of supplies and ammunition. In an emotional message, he likened it to treason" and said there was "direct opposition" to attempts to equip his fighters. Russia's Defence Ministry hit back at those claims and has denied limiting ammunition shipments, calling this "absolutely untrue". FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES: